Data.Text: I KNOW you have all heard of the little Jessica who lived with a gingerbread in kingdom. Just why she lived with it there I don't exactly remember, but I can't imagine that she used to sleep so comfortably with it.

WHEN last we heard of Jessica, do you remember?
"
I don't know what to make of it"" said the gingerbread-dressed gentleman; "but I'm sure there's something in it that makes me giggle."
"Oh" yes"" said Marjorie" as she sat down by the fire and looked out into the glade.

Night come on, blue and then  red, and the waves never tired of their ceaseless jigging.
It was a glorious day for all kinds of little islands" but not one of them had ever been more beautiful than our own kingdom.
The king and queen were sitting in the fire-place at sunset when they heard voices saying: "We have come to save you!"
"No"" answered the princess" "I am not afraid of anything; but I think it would be better if we had a palace fire."
And some day, when you, too, have grown up and have a wonderful gingerbread and have come into a kingdom of your own, you will live-as they lived-happily ever after.
